    <div class="card-info" id="cardInfo">
    <h2>Charles J H Nicolle</h2>
    <p><strong>Lifetime:</strong> 1866–1936</p>
    <p><strong>Title:</strong> Pioneer of Typhus Studies</p>
    <p><strong>Achievements:</strong> Charles Jules Henri Nicolle (1866–1936) made a groundbreaking discovery in the field of infectious diseases.  In 1909, while studying typhus outbreaks in Tunisia, Nicolle demonstrated that the disease was transmitted by body lice (Pediculus humanus corporis). This discovery, made through meticulous experiments involving monkeys and lice, revolutionized our understanding of typhus transmission and led to the development of preventive measures, such as delousing, which significantly reduced the incidence of this deadly disease.</p>
    <p><strong>Legacy:</strong> Charles Jules Henri Nicolle (1866–1936) left a lasting legacy in the field of infectious diseases.  His most significant contribution was the discovery that typhus fever is transmitted by body lice, a groundbreaking finding that revolutionized our understanding of the disease and led to the development of preventive measures, such as delousing, which significantly reduced the incidence of typhus.  Nicolle's work also extended to other areas of research, including brucellosis, leishmaniasis, measles, rinderpest, scarlet fever, Mediterranean spotted fever, toxoplasmosis, trachoma, and tuberculosis. He is also credited with identifying the phenomenon of "inapparent infection," a state in which a carrier of a disease exhibits no symptoms, which has become a critical concept in understanding the epidemiology of many infectious diseases.</p>
</div>


    <script>
        const card = document.getElementById('gameCard');
        const cardInfo = document.getElementById('cardInfo');

        card.addEventListener('click', () => {
            card.classList.toggle('is-flipped');
            cardInfo.classList.toggle('visible');
        });
    </script>

